Hipotese 1

u1 = AVG(SRTF(tat_per_cpu)) u2 = AVG(FCFS(tat_per_cpu))

H0: u1 = u2 H1: u1 < u2

#Load data

wk = load_workload("h1",all_seeds = TRUE)
wk$scheduler = as.factor(wk$scheduler)
wk$workload = as.factor(wk$workload)
wk = select(wk,scheduler,seed,tat_per_cpu)

#Agrupar os dados

wka = aggregate(. ~scheduler+seed,data=wk,mean,na.rm=TRUE)
srtf = wka[wka$scheduler=="SRTF",]
fcfs = wka[wka$scheduler=="FCFS",]

Testar normalidade

Para n>30, pelo TLC podemos assumir normalidade. Caso contrário, podemos testar com, por exemplo, o Shapiro-test

shapiro.test(fcfs$tat_per_cpu)

    Shapiro-Wilk normality test

data:  fcfs$tat_per_cpu
W = 0.96413, p-value = 0.3031
shapiro.test(srtf$tat_per_cpu)

    Shapiro-Wilk normality test

data:  srtf$tat_per_cpu
W = 0.97636, p-value = 0.6386
ggqqplot(fcfs$tat_per_cpu)

ggqqplot(srtf$tat_per_cpu)

#Paired T-test

t.test(
  srtf$tat_per_cpu, fcfs$tat_per_cpu, paired = TRUE, alternative = "less"
)

    Paired t-test

data:  srtf$tat_per_cpu and fcfs$tat_per_cpu
t = -6.3282, df = 34, p-value = 1.619e-07
alternative hypothesis: true difference in means is less than 0
95 percent confidence interval:
       -Inf -0.6844973
sample estimates:
mean of the differences 
             -0.9340883 
gen_density_by_scheduler(wk,"tat_per_cpu")

Hipotese 1.1

Achamos que não vai haver diferença significativa entre SJF e SRTF, mesmo um sendo preenptive e o outro não

u1 = AVG(SRTF(ready_wait_time/nbursts)) u2 = AVG(SJF(ready_wait_time/nbursts))

H0: u1 = u2 H1: u1 != u2

sjf = wka[wka$scheduler=="SJF",]
shapiro.test(sjf$tat_per_cpu)

    Shapiro-Wilk normality test

data:  sjf$tat_per_cpu
W = 0.97713, p-value = 0.6641
t.test(
  srtf$tat_per_cpu, sjf$tat_per_cpu, paired = TRUE
)

    Paired t-test

data:  srtf$tat_per_cpu and sjf$tat_per_cpu
t = -0.69331, df = 34, p-value = 0.4928
alternative hypothesis: true difference in means is not equal to 0
95 percent confidence interval:
 -0.09513619  0.04673599
sample estimates:
mean of the differences 
             -0.0242001
